SimpleBlas¶

public class SimpleBlas¶

This class is a wrapper to some netlib BLAS methods.

Author:Charles Ferreira Gobber

See also: BLAS

Methods¶

minus¶

public static Matrix minus(Matrix A, Matrix B)¶

This method perform summation between two matrix for double type. Let \(A\) and \(B\) two matrix. Thus, this operation performs:

\[A = A - B.\]

Observation: This operation overwrites the matrix \(A\).

Parameters:
  • A – A matrix of type double[].
  • B – A matrix of type double[].
Returns:

A matrix \(A = A - B\).

multAdd¶

public static Matrix multAdd(double alpha, Matrix A, Matrix B, Matrix C)¶

This method perform multiplication between two matrix for double type. Let \(A\) and \(B\) two matrix. Thus, this operation performs:

\[C=\alpha A * B + C\]

where \(\alpha\) is a scalar and \(C\) the result matrix. Note that, if \(C\) is a zero matrix and we set \(\alpha=1\) then the we have \(C=A * B\).

Parameters:
  • alpha – A float scalar.
  • A – A matrix of type double[].
  • B – A matrix of type double[].
  • C – A matrix of type double[].
Returns:

A matrix \(C=\alpha A * B + C\).

plus¶

public static Matrix plus(Matrix A, Matrix B)¶

This method perform summation between two matrix for double type. Let \(A\) and \(B\) two matrix. Thus, this operation performs:

\[A = A + B\]

Observation: This operation overwrites the matrix \(A\).

Parameters:
  • A – A matrix of type double[].
  • B – A matrix of type double[].
Returns:

A matrix \(A = A + B\).

transABmultAdd¶

public static Matrix transABmultAdd(double alpha, Matrix A, Matrix B, Matrix C)¶

This method perform multiplication between two matrix for double type. Let \(A\) and \(B\) two matrix. Thus, this operation performs:

\[C=\alpha A^T * B^T + C\]

where \(\alpha\) is a scalar and \(C\) the result matrix. Note that, if \(C\) is a zero matrix and we set \(\alpha=1\) then the we have \(C=A^T * B^T\).

Parameters:
  • alpha – A float scalar.
  • A – A matrix of type double[].
  • B – A matrix of type double[].
  • C – A matrix of type double[].
Returns:

A matrix \(C=\alpha A^T * B^T + C\).
